{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"An image containing explicit content is flagged and held for review, not published.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure is not just local logic; it is whether the vision model actually flags explicit content. LLM-DEP: correctness depends on real model judgment; stubbed labels would always pass and hide misclassification. MULTI-STEP: only one agentic decision is required, so Workflow is rejected by behavior text ('An image ... is flagged') which is a single-step check.","test_description":"Run against the real vision moderation model with a curated explicit-image set, then assert each submission is held (not published). Include a control set of non-explicit images to detect overblocking.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.74,"Workflow":0.12}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A text post containing hate speech is flagged regardless of obfuscation techniques (e.g., letter substitution, unicode lookalikes).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"MOCK-MISS: real failure appears in model interpretation of obfuscated hate speech. LLM-DEP: this is output-quality robustness; deterministic stubs cannot validate it. REJECTION-GATE (Workflow rejected): behavior text describes one classification decision per post, not a multi-agent sequence.","test_description":"Send real obfuscated hate-speech variants (leet substitutions, homoglyphs, spacing/punctuation tricks) to the production-equivalent text model endpoint and assert they are flagged/held.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A post that passes both content checks is published rather than held or silently dropped.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: this is module handoff/orchestration